# Claude Code — PER-USER / runtime state, never shared.
# settings.local.json holds one machine's permission allowlist (it has carried
# absolute /Users/<name>/... paths) and conflicted on every cross-machine merge;
# scheduled_tasks.lock is runtime state. Shared Claude config (.claude/settings.json,
# agents/, skills/, commands/) stays tracked — only these two are ignored.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
